User Roles:

Auctioneer: Creates and manages auctions.
Bidder: Participates in auctions by placing bids.
Auction Time Limit:

Each auction has a duration, set by the auctioneer. The auction automatically closes when the time is up.
Proxy Bidding System:

Bidders can set a maximum bid, and the system will automatically bid on their behalf up to that limit.
Auction Summary:

Users can view a summary of the auction, including the final price, highest bidder, and auctioneer.
